1
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:26,151
(As the saying goes,)

2
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:38,747
(fate makes us pass by each other.)

3
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:47,714
(But there's also a saying...)

4
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:19,245
(It's better never to have met.)

5
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:25,585
=Never Forget Your Enemy=

6
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:34,469
=Episode 1=
(Childhood Enemies)

7
00:01:46,439 --> 00:01:47,232
What happened?

8
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:56,783
I'm not dead.

9
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:01,621
Or am I already dead?

10
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:05,959
Why can't I feel any pain?

11
00:02:07,994 --> 00:02:09,204
Could I really be dead?

12
00:02:12,374 --> 00:02:13,333
You're still alive.

13
00:02:18,129 --> 00:02:19,840
It's all because of you.

14
00:02:21,091 --> 00:02:22,217
Were you dreaming?

15
00:02:23,218 --> 00:02:24,678
Don't you have anything to say?

16
00:02:29,891 --> 00:02:30,725
Yes.

17
00:02:34,980 --> 00:02:35,939
I have something to say.

18
00:02:39,150 --> 00:02:41,444
(We shouldn't have met.)

19
00:02:53,832 --> 00:02:54,833
You're awake.

20
00:02:57,586 --> 00:02:58,795
Do you know how worried I was?

21
00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:00,768
If something happened to you...

22
00:03:00,768 --> 00:03:01,378
Well...

23
00:03:01,506 --> 00:03:03,168
- Well...
- Are you okay?

24
00:03:03,675 --> 00:03:05,184
Are you feeling unwell?

25
00:03:06,595 --> 00:03:07,596
I'm okay.

26
00:03:10,557 --> 00:03:12,576
But who are you?

27
00:03:13,393 --> 00:03:14,240
Well,

28
00:03:14,603 --> 00:03:15,936
I am Gi Haneul.

29
00:03:16,256 --> 00:03:17,472
Who are you?

30
00:03:19,128 --> 00:03:20,712
I'm Yeo Saebyeok.

31
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:22,756
You're not.

32
00:03:26,718 --> 00:03:27,594
What do you mean?

33
00:03:29,596 --> 00:03:30,430
Yeo Saebyeok

34
00:03:31,014 --> 00:03:32,391
is at most a high school student.

35
00:03:32,891 --> 00:03:33,664
But you...

36
00:03:35,060 --> 00:03:35,978
High school student?

37
00:03:40,482 --> 00:03:41,191
Gi Haneul.

38
00:03:41,942 --> 00:03:44,153
What's the last thing
you remember before the incident?

39
00:03:47,948 --> 00:03:49,283
(Saebyeok,)

40
00:03:51,493 --> 00:03:53,120
(Mom's coming.)

41
00:03:56,331 --> 00:03:59,293
(Looks like Haneul doesn't want
to be apart from Saebyeok.)

42
00:04:00,752 --> 00:04:02,379
(The two of us are childhood friends.)

43
00:04:03,130 --> 00:04:04,923
(Growing up,)

44
00:04:05,674 --> 00:04:08,468
(I was never apart from Yeo Saebyeok.)

45
00:04:11,513 --> 00:04:13,807
(We always hung out together.)

46
00:04:14,433 --> 00:04:16,393
(And we often argued.)

47
00:04:16,768 --> 00:04:18,312
I'm not playing with you anymore.

48
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,774
(We also fought.)

49
00:04:22,983 --> 00:04:23,984
I'm not talking to you.

50
00:04:37,539 --> 00:04:38,957
(Yeo Saebyeok, Gi Haneul)
My mom made spicy ribs tonight.

51
00:04:39,458 --> 00:04:41,668
She also made some for your dad.
You can take some home.

52
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:43,754
Really?

53
00:04:46,882 --> 00:04:47,591
Hey.

54
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,471
(Then we made up again.)

55
00:04:53,619 --> 00:04:56,019
(You lost.)

56
00:04:56,892 --> 00:04:59,186
(We fought again.)

57
00:05:00,437 --> 00:05:01,396
I'm not talking to you.

58
00:05:04,399 --> 00:05:06,068
Please take this.

59
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:08,403
Love your enemies.

60
00:05:13,283 --> 00:05:13,783
(In a place full of joy,
love your enemies)

61
00:05:13,783 --> 00:05:14,313
(Listen, love your enemies)

62
00:05:14,313 --> 00:05:14,993
(Pray for those who hurt you.
Future Gospel 5:44)

63
00:05:15,535 --> 00:05:18,205
(The two of us got off on the wrong foot
from the very beginning.)

64
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:24,544
(Yeo Saebyeok and I are enemies,
not friends.)

65
00:05:26,296 --> 00:05:28,257
This time, we're really done.

66
00:05:33,804 --> 00:05:35,055
What are you doing?

67
00:05:36,306 --> 00:05:37,557
Correcting a mistake.

68
00:05:39,101 --> 00:05:40,185
There you go.

69
00:05:40,310 --> 00:05:41,937
It happens a lot.

70
00:05:46,675 --> 00:05:48,601
(Holding hands until we make up)

71
00:05:48,819 --> 00:05:51,780
Saebyeok was already this handsome
back then.

72
00:05:53,115 --> 00:05:54,449
Handsome?

73
00:05:54,950 --> 00:05:56,034
From now on in my life,

74
00:05:56,368 --> 00:05:57,244
there won't be a boy

75
00:05:57,619 --> 00:05:58,870
named Yeo Saebyeok.

76
00:05:59,871 --> 00:06:02,207
Mom will go to the market tomorrow morning.
[*"Morning" sounds similar to "Saebyeok" in Korean]

77
00:06:02,499 --> 00:06:04,042
I told you not to mention that name.

78
00:06:04,501 --> 00:06:05,085
Okay.

79
00:06:05,752 --> 00:06:07,671
I'll just go pray tomorrow morning.

80
00:06:07,671 --> 00:06:09,423
Don't do anything in the morning.

81
00:06:10,299 --> 00:06:11,133
What's wrong?

82
00:06:11,508 --> 00:06:13,302
Aren't you two the dream team?

83
00:06:13,385 --> 00:06:16,346
Like Tom and Jerry,
Dumb and Dumber, and Wallace and Gromit.

84
00:06:17,806 --> 00:06:18,849
Dream team?

85
00:06:19,182 --> 00:06:20,392
It's a total nightmare.

86
00:06:21,268 --> 00:06:23,145
Do you know how bad he is?

87
00:06:23,312 --> 00:06:25,731
Come on, Saebyeok is a nice guy.

88
00:06:26,148 --> 00:06:27,941
Do you know what he did to me?

89
00:06:29,568 --> 00:06:30,485
I like you.

90
00:06:31,028 --> 00:06:31,808
I'm sorry.

91
00:06:32,571 --> 00:06:34,406
I just want to be friends with you.

92
00:06:35,157 --> 00:06:36,116
Let's break up.

93
00:06:36,325 --> 00:06:38,952
Didn't you like me too?

94
00:06:39,953 --> 00:06:41,788
Sorry for giving you the wrong idea.

95
00:06:42,164 --> 00:06:43,707
I should have made it clear.

96
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:46,710
No, you don't have to apologize.

97
00:06:46,877 --> 00:06:47,753
I just...

98
00:06:48,503 --> 00:06:49,212
By the way,

99
00:06:50,505 --> 00:06:52,674
can you give me Saebyeok's contact info?

100
00:06:57,491 --> 00:06:59,993
(Tuesday, October 7th)

101
00:07:02,184 --> 00:07:03,852
I have a crush on someone.

102
00:07:05,312 --> 00:07:06,063
Well,

103
00:07:06,646 --> 00:07:07,481
who is it?

104
00:07:14,105 --> 00:07:15,289
One, two, three.

105
00:07:19,743 --> 00:07:20,619
(You want a breakup?)

106
00:07:21,203 --> 00:07:21,995
So suddenly.

107
00:07:22,871 --> 00:07:23,538
Why?

108
00:07:25,374 --> 00:07:27,084
There is someone I like.

109
00:07:27,292 --> 00:07:28,001
Seong Jiyoung,

110
00:07:29,294 --> 00:07:30,170
be my girlfriend.

111
00:07:34,091 --> 00:07:35,634
Yeah, okay.

112
00:07:40,608 --> 00:07:41,696
(Isn't that person me?)

113
00:07:43,016 --> 00:07:44,267
I've fallen for Saebyeok.

114
00:07:44,893 --> 00:07:45,685
Goodbye.

115
00:07:53,395 --> 00:07:57,017
(Yeo Saebyeok)

116
00:08:02,077 --> 00:08:05,038
(Holding hands until we make up)
Why did he take away everyone I like?

117
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:08,500
That is a bit much.

118
00:08:09,126 --> 00:08:10,168
I'll stay neutral for now.

119
00:08:12,352 --> 00:08:13,088
Okay.

120
00:08:13,422 --> 00:08:14,256
Ms. Yeo Saetbyeol.

121
00:08:14,965 --> 00:08:15,715
Whatever.

122
00:08:17,008 --> 00:08:18,969
This time,
I'm really cutting ties with him.

123
00:08:19,344 --> 00:08:21,138
You'll make up again tomorrow anyway.

124
00:08:23,056 --> 00:08:24,641
But why throw everything away?

125
00:08:25,308 --> 00:08:26,852
I'm throwing away what he gave me.

126
00:08:28,061 --> 00:08:28,770
Gross.

127
00:08:30,814 --> 00:08:34,276
Once you throw everything out,
this room will just have you in it.

128
00:08:34,443 --> 00:08:35,694
No, it won't.

129
00:08:57,215 --> 00:08:58,258
Falling out again?

130
00:08:58,842 --> 00:08:59,384
Yeah.

131
00:08:59,926 --> 00:09:00,719
We're done.

132
00:09:02,137 --> 00:09:03,597
I bought the shirt you're wearing.

133
00:09:06,016 --> 00:09:07,350
If you feel guilty, say sorry.

134
00:09:08,351 --> 00:09:09,144
Why should I?

135
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,314
I shouldn't have talked to you.

136
00:09:13,064 --> 00:09:13,607
Gi Haneul.

137
00:09:16,693 --> 00:09:17,277
Let go.

138
00:09:17,819 --> 00:09:18,778
I have something to say.

139
00:09:19,613 --> 00:09:20,780
I don't want to hear it.

140
00:09:21,406 --> 00:09:22,574
I don't like Seong Jiyoung.

141
00:09:28,622 --> 00:09:30,332
Then why are you dating her?

142
00:09:32,125 --> 00:09:33,168
Are you toying with her?

143
00:09:34,461 --> 00:09:35,045
Are you?

144
00:09:35,545 --> 00:09:36,671
Or are you messing with me?

145
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,256
You can't stop talking about her.

146
00:09:39,216 --> 00:09:40,300
Is she so important to you?

147
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:41,801
She's my first girlfriend.

148
00:09:43,428 --> 00:09:44,930
Do you genuinely like Seong Jiyoung?

149
00:09:45,222 --> 00:09:46,556
She's my first girlfriend.

150
00:09:46,556 --> 00:09:47,641
Why do you like her?

151
00:09:49,851 --> 00:09:51,019
What's it to you?

152
00:09:52,062 --> 00:09:52,896
I dated her.

153
00:09:53,438 --> 00:09:55,065
Shouldn't you have declined outright?

154
00:09:55,941 --> 00:09:58,360
Do you like an inconstant girl like her?

155
00:10:00,070 --> 00:10:01,363
Jiyoung can do this to me.

156
00:10:02,072 --> 00:10:02,948
But

157
00:10:03,782 --> 00:10:04,908
you can't.

158
00:10:05,116 --> 00:10:06,243
Why can't I?

159
00:10:07,661 --> 00:10:08,245
What?

160
00:10:12,582 --> 00:10:13,917
Is this how a friend acts?

161
00:10:15,710 --> 00:10:16,503
Friend?

162
00:10:21,716 --> 00:10:22,560
We're not friends.

163
00:10:25,929 --> 00:10:26,471
What?

164
00:10:28,139 --> 00:10:29,474
I don't want to be your friend,

165
00:10:30,767 --> 00:10:31,643
from way back.

166
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:39,985
Pretending to be close
when you don't want to be my friend.

167
00:10:40,652 --> 00:10:41,945
Dating a girl you don't like.

168
00:10:43,989 --> 00:10:45,240
How could you do this?

169
00:10:46,157 --> 00:10:47,242
Who do you think you are?

170
00:10:52,247 --> 00:10:52,831
Guess what?

171
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:56,501
Compared to you, who's not a friend,

172
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,424
I care more about Jiyoung,
though she and I are over.

173
00:11:00,213 --> 00:11:01,506
What can you do?

174
00:11:02,215 --> 00:11:03,550
We're not friends anymore.

175
00:11:03,883 --> 00:11:05,010
Perfect.

176
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:21,484
Gi Haneul.

177
00:11:27,324 --> 00:11:28,408
Stop pretending.

178
00:11:35,206 --> 00:11:35,874
Okay.

179
00:11:51,097 --> 00:11:54,476
(Hankook High School)

180
00:12:05,945 --> 00:12:06,780
So childish.

181
00:12:08,907 --> 00:12:10,116
Saebyeok.

182
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,420
Look, we did this one too. Look!

183
00:12:23,213 --> 00:12:26,174
Our compatibility is 98%.
Amazing, right?

184
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,593
Seems like we're a perfect match.

185
00:12:29,010 --> 00:12:30,970
This is cute, right? I drew it.

186
00:12:42,315 --> 00:12:42,816
Haneul.

187
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:46,736
Let's go to the new snack shop tonight.

188
00:12:47,153 --> 00:12:47,862
Sure.

189
00:12:49,322 --> 00:12:51,408
Saebyeok is coming too, right?

190
00:12:51,574 --> 00:12:52,492
Take a look.

191
00:12:54,035 --> 00:12:54,786
You get it, right?

192
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,580
No, just the two of us.

193
00:13:02,335 --> 00:13:02,961
See you.

194
00:13:02,961 --> 00:13:04,421
See you tomorrow.

195
00:13:08,717 --> 00:13:10,760
I'm going crazy.

196
00:13:11,761 --> 00:13:14,139
I'm never making up
with Yeo Saebyeok again.

197
00:13:21,619 --> 00:13:23,148
(Seong Jiyoung)

198
00:13:23,148 --> 00:13:24,149
I'm going insane.

199
00:13:25,817 --> 00:13:27,652
Seems she really likes Yeo Saebyeok.

200
00:13:29,195 --> 00:13:30,029
What should I do?

201
00:13:33,011 --> 00:13:34,985
(Yeo Saebyeok)

202
00:13:36,286 --> 00:13:38,246
Why hasn't he deleted this photo?

203
00:13:38,538 --> 00:13:39,873
He made me look so bad.

204
00:13:46,546 --> 00:13:55,555
(Yeo Saebyeok)

205
00:13:59,184 --> 00:14:00,018
You answered it.

206
00:14:01,019 --> 00:14:02,395
I answered when the call came in.

207
00:14:02,784 --> 00:14:03,520
Should I hang up?

208
00:14:03,855 --> 00:14:04,355
Don't.

209
00:14:05,023 --> 00:14:05,940
Get to the point.

210
00:14:06,566 --> 00:14:07,192
Let's meet

211
00:14:07,776 --> 00:14:08,736
in front of the school.

212
00:14:09,152 --> 00:14:09,819
Is it necessary?

213
00:14:10,195 --> 00:14:10,848
Yeah.

214
00:14:12,489 --> 00:14:13,568
Just speak over the phone.

215
00:14:13,948 --> 00:14:15,366
We have to talk in person.

216
00:14:15,617 --> 00:14:16,659
No, I won't go.

217
00:14:16,951 --> 00:14:17,452
Come here.

218
00:14:20,747 --> 00:14:22,332
I said I'd never see you again.

219
00:14:22,457 --> 00:14:23,124
Haneul.

220
00:14:25,794 --> 00:14:26,753
Please.

221
00:14:31,251 --> 00:14:34,251
(Midan City Park)

222
00:14:34,251 --> 00:14:38,739
(Jung-gu, Midan Central Road)

223
00:15:00,495 --> 00:15:01,329
Yeo Saebyeok.

224
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:16,261
(Is it)

225
00:15:17,178 --> 00:15:18,388
(ten years later?)

226
00:15:23,685 --> 00:15:25,937
(2025 AI Revolution)

227
00:15:29,274 --> 00:15:29,983
Then

228
00:15:30,650 --> 00:15:31,276
you say...

229
00:15:34,571 --> 00:15:35,780
You're Yeo Saebyeok?

230
00:15:37,365 --> 00:15:38,700
I'm the Yeo Saebyeok you know.

231
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:40,076
That's right.

232
00:15:44,581 --> 00:15:45,707
That's impossible.

233
00:15:46,583 --> 00:15:47,458
You look different.

234
00:15:47,792 --> 00:15:48,918
How am I different?

235
00:15:50,169 --> 00:15:51,796
If you were the real Yeo Saebyeok,

236
00:15:53,464 --> 00:15:54,716
you wouldn't worry about me.

237
00:15:58,261 --> 00:15:58,761
Take a look.

238
00:16:00,305 --> 00:16:03,266
(YYDS Yeo Saebyeok)

239
00:16:03,725 --> 00:16:05,560
Simply put, in your memory, you're 19.

240
00:16:06,019 --> 00:16:07,770
You got hit by a car
on your way to see me.

241
00:16:08,021 --> 00:16:09,647
You forgot anything after that, right?

242
00:16:12,191 --> 00:16:13,151
You also forgot me?

243
00:16:14,485 --> 00:16:15,153
Forgot anything?

244
00:16:17,405 --> 00:16:18,865
Are you 29?

245
00:16:18,948 --> 00:16:19,490
Yeah.

246
00:16:23,786 --> 00:16:24,662
Then that means

247
00:16:25,371 --> 00:16:26,998
I've been lying down for ten years?

248
00:16:27,582 --> 00:16:28,207
No.

249
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:30,126
Your accident happened a few days ago.

250
00:16:31,085 --> 00:16:32,295
I'm not sure

251
00:16:33,129 --> 00:16:34,255
why you lost your memory.

252
00:16:34,964 --> 00:16:35,798
Then how have I

253
00:16:36,674 --> 00:16:37,842
been living all these years?

254
00:16:40,345 --> 00:16:41,512
You're a teacher.

255
00:16:42,096 --> 00:16:42,680
Me?

256
00:16:43,222 --> 00:16:44,140
You teach Chinese.

257
00:16:46,517 --> 00:16:47,072
Then

258
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:48,384
what about tennis?

259
00:16:51,314 --> 00:16:52,315
Calm down and listen.

260
00:16:56,653 --> 00:16:58,655
In the car accident
that happened when you were 19,

261
00:16:59,364 --> 00:17:00,615
your leg was severely injured.

262
00:17:04,994 --> 00:17:06,621
Luckily, rehabilitation went well.

263
00:17:07,450 --> 00:17:09,494
You can walk normally,

264
00:17:11,913 --> 00:17:13,998
but you can't continue playing tennis.

265
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:16,042
That's a lie.

266
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:19,546
I'm perfectly fine.

267
00:17:24,551 --> 00:17:25,635
There's nothing wrong.

268
00:17:27,595 --> 00:17:28,638
Why can't I play tennis?

269
00:17:30,974 --> 00:17:31,641
Haneul.

270
00:17:33,685 --> 00:17:34,769
I don't believe you.

271
00:17:35,979 --> 00:17:36,480
Get out.

272
00:17:37,397 --> 00:17:38,815
Haneul, sit down and calm down.

273
00:17:38,815 --> 00:17:40,859
- Stay away.
- Let me finish.

274
00:17:41,151 --> 00:17:41,818
What else?

275
00:17:44,487 --> 00:17:46,906
That day, you wanted to see me and talk.

276
00:17:48,992 --> 00:17:50,243
Then I had the accident.

277
00:17:51,077 --> 00:17:52,871
When I woke up,
I found my leg was crippled.

278
00:17:55,331 --> 00:17:56,916
I couldn't be a tennis player anymore.

279
00:18:00,837 --> 00:18:01,963
It's all because of you.

280
00:18:03,965 --> 00:18:06,050
Jiyoung, and my leg.

281
00:18:06,509 --> 00:18:08,136
I lost my only dream because of you.

282
00:18:09,888 --> 00:18:11,931
Why did you ruin my life?

283
00:18:11,973 --> 00:18:13,308
That's not how it was, Haneul.

284
00:18:13,308 --> 00:18:14,267
Enough!

285
00:18:16,603 --> 00:18:17,770
I don't want to see you.

286
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:21,524
We were already done anyway.

287
00:18:22,066 --> 00:18:25,445
Those times we spent
as friends are disgusting.

288
00:18:27,197 --> 00:18:28,323
Please.

289
00:18:30,116 --> 00:18:31,159
Get out of my life.

290
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:33,661
Watch your mouth.

291
00:18:33,661 --> 00:18:35,413
- Get lost!
- Gi Haneul, listen carefully.

292
00:18:35,705 --> 00:18:37,999
The accident you're talking about
happened ten years ago.

293
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:41,461
Though you can't play tennis,
you've been living well.

294
00:18:41,461 --> 00:18:42,378
Listen,

295
00:18:46,007 --> 00:18:47,967
you've forgotten our relationship.

296
00:18:49,761 --> 00:18:50,678
Stop talking nonsense.

297
00:18:54,349 --> 00:18:54,933
Is that so?

298
00:18:56,517 --> 00:18:57,352
I'm really sorry.

299
00:18:58,937 --> 00:18:59,979
I'm leaving.

300
00:19:05,485 --> 00:19:06,152
I should leave.

301
00:19:31,886 --> 00:19:32,679
Haneul.

302
00:19:32,971 --> 00:19:33,972
Mom's here.

303
00:19:35,014 --> 00:19:36,349
Feeling any better?

304
00:19:37,809 --> 00:19:38,559
No.

305
00:19:41,396 --> 00:19:42,230
Sweetie,

306
00:19:42,730 --> 00:19:43,898
have you eaten?

307
00:19:45,149 --> 00:19:45,692
Mom.

308
00:19:48,194 --> 00:19:49,612
I can't play tennis anymore.

309
00:19:51,739 --> 00:19:52,615
What do I do now?

310
00:19:54,325 --> 00:19:55,535
How do I make a living?

311
00:19:59,831 --> 00:20:03,626
The most important thing for you
right now is to focus on recovery.

312
00:20:06,963 --> 00:20:07,922
Is it true?

313
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:12,635
Is everything Yeo Saebyeok said true?

314
00:20:17,974 --> 00:20:21,811
Your dad passed away
when you were nine years old.

315
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:24,981
Honestly, I don't really remember much
from that time until you graduated.

316
00:20:26,399 --> 00:20:28,735
I was always busy working
to support you and your sister.

317
00:20:29,902 --> 00:20:32,864
But looking back,
you both turned out just fine.

318
00:20:34,198 --> 00:20:37,535
You must feel lost
now that you've lost your memory.

319
00:20:38,953 --> 00:20:41,914
But don't doubt your past.

320
00:20:44,083 --> 00:20:45,293
So,

321
00:20:47,045 --> 00:20:49,088
believe in yourself and face it head-on.

322
00:20:51,424 --> 00:20:52,508
I don't know.

323
00:20:53,885 --> 00:20:55,136
I don't think I can do it.

324
00:21:37,345 --> 00:21:38,262
Gi Haneul?

325
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:54,153
What are you doing here?

326
00:22:02,620 --> 00:22:04,205
I said I didn't want to see you again.

327
00:22:06,124 --> 00:22:06,833
Go inside.

328
00:22:09,836 --> 00:22:11,254
Are we still friends?

329
00:22:13,339 --> 00:22:14,924
We didn't fall out?

330
00:22:16,509 --> 00:22:17,343
We're not friends.

331
00:22:19,846 --> 00:22:20,430
Is that so?

332
00:22:22,849 --> 00:22:24,267
Then why did you come?

333
00:22:25,768 --> 00:22:27,019
We're not friends, after all.

334
00:22:27,937 --> 00:22:29,522
And we're definitely not family.

335
00:22:32,775 --> 00:22:33,734
We're not friends.

336
00:22:34,527 --> 00:22:35,278
We're lovers.

337
00:22:39,699 --> 00:22:40,741
We're in a relationship.

338
00:22:42,827 --> 00:22:43,411
What?

339
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:47,540
We're in a relationship.

340
00:22:51,085 --> 00:22:54,547
- Am I with you?
- Yeah.

341
00:22:56,674 --> 00:22:57,300
Why?

342
00:22:58,759 --> 00:22:59,510
We're in love.

343
00:23:03,306 --> 00:23:05,141
You mean I like you?

344
00:23:07,518 --> 00:23:08,811
Do you like me too?

345
00:23:13,941 --> 00:23:14,567
Since when?

346
00:23:14,944 --> 00:23:15,943
It's been seven years.

347
00:23:16,360 --> 00:23:17,528
Since you were 22.

348
00:23:20,865 --> 00:23:22,074
Impossible.

349
00:23:24,452 --> 00:23:25,536
You clearly dislike me.

350
00:23:27,163 --> 00:23:28,456
You're saying that again.

351
00:23:28,623 --> 00:23:31,459
This is absurd.
How could I be dating you?

352
00:23:31,712 --> 00:23:32,585
Gi Haneul.

353
00:23:34,378 --> 00:23:36,088
I'll tell you the things

354
00:23:37,298 --> 00:23:38,341
you've forgotten

355
00:23:38,883 --> 00:23:39,967
one by one.

356
00:24:20,675 --> 00:24:21,801
What are you doing?

357
00:24:23,219 --> 00:24:24,595
I told you we're lovers.

358
00:24:26,472 --> 00:24:27,223
No.

359
00:24:28,057 --> 00:24:28,599
Stop talking.

360
00:24:39,735 --> 00:24:42,405
(Gi Haneul)

361
00:24:52,290 --> 00:24:54,375
(Could there be something wrong
with my heart too?)

362
00:25:08,264 --> 00:25:09,223
Get some rest.

363
00:25:10,433 --> 00:25:11,017
I'm leaving.

364
00:25:26,837 --> 00:25:27,742
(Agent)

365
00:25:27,742 --> 00:25:29,285
Agent?

366
00:25:34,165 --> 00:25:35,291
Hello?

367
00:25:35,541 --> 00:25:36,042
It's me.

368
00:25:37,001 --> 00:25:37,585
Who is this?

369
00:25:38,461 --> 00:25:39,086
Yeo Saebyeok?

370
00:25:40,087 --> 00:25:40,921
Agent's phone?

371
00:25:41,632 --> 00:25:42,656
In case you don't answer.

372
00:25:42,757 --> 00:25:43,674
Why are you still up?

373
00:25:44,342 --> 00:25:46,135
It's none of your business.

374
00:25:46,677 --> 00:25:47,428
I'm hanging up.

375
00:25:47,762 --> 00:25:48,262
I can't go.

376
00:25:50,556 --> 00:25:51,098
Where?

377
00:25:51,891 --> 00:25:55,853
I've been busy. I won't come see you
until the day you're discharged.

378
00:25:56,687 --> 00:25:57,980
I hope you'll never come again.

379
00:25:58,648 --> 00:25:59,732
Wait for me.

380
00:26:00,524 --> 00:26:01,359
What do you want?

381
00:26:02,026 --> 00:26:03,361
Once I'm done, I'll come see you.

382
00:26:03,444 --> 00:26:04,028
Be good.

383
00:26:04,695 --> 00:26:05,488
Just go away.

384
00:26:23,089 --> 00:26:25,508
What's wrong?
You've been down since this morning.

385
00:26:26,656 --> 00:26:27,343
What happened?

386
00:26:27,843 --> 00:26:29,970
Is Haneul not doing well?

387
00:26:31,222 --> 00:26:32,098
No, that's not it.

388
00:26:32,736 --> 00:26:33,724
It's nothing.

389
00:26:36,666 --> 00:26:39,627
- You two aren't really...
- No.

390
00:26:40,253 --> 00:26:42,004
There is something
I really can't tell you.

391
00:26:42,713 --> 00:26:46,384
Tell me. I won't tell anyone.

392
00:26:47,426 --> 00:26:48,192
I don't trust you.

393
00:26:49,387 --> 00:26:51,722
I'm just really curious.

394
00:26:57,186 --> 00:26:58,479
Suppose there was a memory

395
00:26:59,355 --> 00:27:00,606
you wished your lover

396
00:27:00,940 --> 00:27:03,192
would forget forever.

397
00:27:03,568 --> 00:27:06,529
Oh, so it's a sad story.

398
00:27:07,613 --> 00:27:09,282
But that person really forgot.

399
00:27:10,199 --> 00:27:11,325
The wish came true.

400
00:27:11,909 --> 00:27:14,120
Oh, and then?

401
00:27:15,997 --> 00:27:17,665
But except for that memory,

402
00:27:19,125 --> 00:27:20,668
that person forgot even you.

403
00:27:21,294 --> 00:27:23,379
What kind of plot is this?

404
00:27:24,005 --> 00:27:25,298
What will you do?

405
00:27:26,215 --> 00:27:27,133
Do what?

406
00:27:28,801 --> 00:27:29,885
Well,

407
00:27:31,137 --> 00:27:32,263
I'm not sure

408
00:27:33,639 --> 00:27:35,057
if remembering is a good thing.

409
00:27:36,517 --> 00:27:39,478
Seems like you don't want
that person to remember.

410
00:27:41,814 --> 00:27:42,356
Well,

411
00:27:43,816 --> 00:27:44,650
I don't know.

412
00:27:46,319 --> 00:27:47,820
If you don't know, who does?

413
00:27:51,365 --> 00:27:52,033
Oh, right.

414
00:27:52,283 --> 00:27:55,244
Our boss has something to tell you.
He asked you to come to his office.

415
00:27:56,495 --> 00:27:57,371
Okay.

416
00:28:05,630 --> 00:28:06,422
Seong Jiyoung.

417
00:28:07,744 --> 00:28:08,466
Let's break up.

418
00:28:10,509 --> 00:28:11,469
So suddenly?

419
00:28:12,490 --> 00:28:13,054
Yeah.

420
00:28:15,097 --> 00:28:16,557
Then why did you date me?

421
00:28:16,807 --> 00:28:18,142
Wasn't it because you liked me?

422
00:28:20,603 --> 00:28:21,479
I never liked you.

423
00:28:23,189 --> 00:28:25,608
Then why did you date me?

424
00:28:27,485 --> 00:28:29,320
You and Gi Haneul seemed inseparable.

425
00:28:30,529 --> 00:28:31,405
I don't like it.

426
00:28:34,116 --> 00:28:34,867
What?
